# Environment Constraints & Command Syntax

You are operating in a **PowerShell** environment on Windows. These constraints will save you time and prevent execution errors.

## Command Chaining

PowerShell uses semicolons (`;`) instead of ampersands (`&&`) for command chaining.

**INCORRECT:**
```powershell
git add . && git commit -m "message" && git tag exp_01
```

**CORRECT:**
```powershell
git add .; git commit -m "message"; git tag exp_01
```

