## Multi-line Git Commits

PowerShell struggles with Bash-style heredocs and complex quoting for multi-line strings.

**AVOID (will fail in PowerShell):**
```powershell
git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
Multi-line
message
here
EOF
)"
```

**USE INSTEAD:**

Option 1 - Single line:
```powershell
git commit -m "Brief description of changes"
```

Option 2 - Multiple `-m` flags:
```powershell
git commit -m "Feature: Title" -m "Description line 1" -m "Description line 2"
```

